---
import Main from "@/layouts/Main.astro";
---

<Main title="Print Tips | Bible Games">
  <section class="panel info-page info-page-dark">
    <h1 class="title">Printing Advice</h1>

    <p>
      Most puzzles are designed to fit on one page, but some verses are longer and may need a quick print adjustment.
    </p>

    <p>
      If your print preview spills to a second page, first try switching orientation:
    </p>

    <p>
      Portrait works best for Word Search and Verse Unscramble.
      <br />
      Landscape works best for Cryptogram.
    </p>

    <p>
      You can also use your browser print dialog scaling settings:
    </p>

    <p>
      Open Print, then lower scale a little (for example from 100% to 95% or 90%) until everything fits on one page.
    </p>

    <p>
      If needed, reduce margins in the print dialog as well.
    </p>

    <p><a href="/">Click here to go back to the games</a></p>
  </section>

  <style>
    .info-page {
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      line-height: 1.65;
    }

    .info-page-dark {
      background: linear-gradient(180deg, #103f36 0%, #0d342d 100%);
      border-color: #123a30;
      color: #e9f6f1;
    }

    .info-page-dark .title,
    .info-page-dark .subtitle {
      color: #f0fffa;
    }

    .info-page p {
      margin-top: 0.9rem;
      margin-bottom: 0.9rem;
    }
  </style>
</Main>
